      "content": "The argument that childcare or transportation is the main issue is a well-established, but ultimately secondary, critique. While those barriers exist, the incentive problem created by benefit cliffs is the more fundamental structural failure. When the government's support system actively punishes work through benefit withdrawal, no amount of subsidized childcare can overcome that economic disincentive. The system is designed to reward dependency over productivity.",
